> mvn archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.xpertians.sample -DartifactId=sample-app -DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

Add the POM
> cd maven/sample-app/
> mvn clean package

For testing:
> mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.xpertians.sample.App"


For generating an SBOM:

For Cyclone DX:
	        <!-- CycloneDX Maven Plugin -->
	        <plugin>
	            <groupId>org.cyclonedx</groupId>
	            <artifactId>cyclonedx-maven-plugin</artifactId>
	            <version>2.7.4</version>
	            <executions>
	                <execution>
	                    <phase>package</phase>
	                    <goals>
	                        <goal>makeAggregateBom</goal>
	                    </goals>
	                </execution>
	            </executions>
	        </plugin>
			
Then, generate SBOMs:
> mvn clean package cyclonedx:makeAggregateBom

Using tooling to convert the SBOM into notices:

a) Using Pom2Notices.py:
>  python3 bom2notices.py

b) Using SPDX tools:
1) convert CycloneDX into SPDX:
https://github.com/CycloneDX/cyclonedx-cli/releases
> ./cyclonedx-osx-x64 convert --input-format xml --output-format spdxjson --input-file target/bom.xml --output-file target/bom.spdx.json
> java -jar tools-java-2.0.0-Alpha-jar-with-dependencies.jar convert --input-file ../target/bom.xml --output-format tag --output-file legal_attribution.txt

